places.name: Dar es Salaam Zoo
places.perex: Encounter the Tanzanian wildlife conveniently. Your children will be amazed by the variety of animals in their natural habitats.

Mbalamwezi Beach Club
places.perex: The most popular beach club attracts a mixed crowd eager to party, sunbathe or just enjoy the sea. A wonderful place.

places.name: Mangapwani Coral Cave
places.perex: This site is full of history - it used to be a hub of slave trade, the prospective slaves were kept in it.

places.name: Jozani Sea Turtle and Tortoise Sanctuary
Kunduchi Wet 'N' Wild Water Park
places.perex: If you don't apply American theme park standards, you won't be disappointed. A lovely place to take your children to.

places.name: Breezes Beach Club
places.perex: Top-notch beach club that offers probably the most luxurious service on the island. Everything from a spa to scuba diving.

places.name: Bilicanas
places.perex: This place is real, bustling and packed every night. The most popular night-time spot in the city.

places.name: The Tanzanite Dream
places.perex: The most credible shop where to buy tanzanite, the precious gemstone so characteristic for this country. Amazing variety of jewellery.

places.name: Botanical Garden
places.perex: These gardens were laid out during the German colonial era. Beautiful stretch of well manicured lush vegetation.

places.name: Bunge
places.perex: The Tanzanian parliament resides in this impressive building that should finally be earthquake-proof.

places.name: Mrembo Spa
places.perex: This pleasant spa offers not only your typical treatments but incorporates also local traditional approaches and herbs.

places.name: Cinnamon Spa
places.perex: Luxurious and yet unpretentious - this spa will soothe your body and sweep daily problems from your mind.

places.name: Kaole Ruins
places.perex: Ruins of the oldest mosque in East Africa are surrounded by tombstones. There is an old, long unused port, too.

places.name: Karimjee Hall
places.perex: The officially-looking building served as a seat of Tanzanian parliament. Stop by and marvel at its unique features.

places.name: South Beach
places.perex: One of the most popular beaches in Tanzania - so vast that it never gets really crowded. You can also watch fishermen in action.

places.name: Mbweni Ruins
places.perex: Atmospheric ruins of 19th century mission station that provided shelter to the former slaves. Very moving place.

places.name: Ilala Market
places.perex: Come here to taste the real Tanzanian life. Local market offering a large selection of goods necessary for the locals.

places.name: Jangwani Beach
places.perex: Luxurious resort beach attracts people for its translucent water and fine, silvery sand. A beautiful place.

places.name: Ras Mkumbi Lighthouse
places.perex: Built by the Germans, this red-and-white light is still active and can be visited. Its location is spectacular, too.

places.name: Mwenge Woodarvers Market
places.perex: The name just says it all: this is the best place to purchase the beautiful products made by Tanzanian craftsmen.

places.name: Ras Kisimani
places.perex: What breath-taking remains of historical heritage. Long eroded, almost gone, but still impressive ruins that once were a powerful city.

places.name: Kombangulu
places.perex: Totally off the beaten path and difficult to find yet well worth it - its rocks are covered with beautiful paintings.

places.name: Gangilonga Rock
places.perex: Interestingly shaped rock that will allow you to see the spectacular panorama Tanzanian nature has to offer.

places.name: Lion Rock
places.perex: If you travel in a larger group, consider climbing the Lion Rock aka Simba Hill. The views of the city are well worth it.

places.name: Jibondo
places.perex: One of the few inhabited islands in the area. Definitely pay a visit to its fishing village - like a journey back in time.

places.name: Isimila Gorge
places.perex: A Stone Age site easily recognisable for its spectacular rock formations. An important place that has been inhabited since 60,000 years ago.

places.name: Bwejuu Island
places.perex: Tiny but enchanting island surrounded with spectacular reefs full of abundant life. What a paradise!
